body:
I ran into this error while testing some new [ROHD](https://github.com/intel/rohd) SystemVerilog generation for `wire`s.  The goal is a module which can support a bidirectional replication operation for nets.

> sorry: I do not know how to elaborate repeat concatenation nets.

It looks like it's coming from here:
https://github.com/steveicarus/iverilog/blob/d8c3c51ab1190ed3fb26540d7de6177f83e0e75b/elab_net.cc#L54-L58

Here's a small testbench that reproduces the issue and should pass if the feature were implemented.

```SystemVerilog
module net_connect #(parameter WIDTH=1) (w, w); 
inout wire[WIDTH-1:0] w;
endmodule

////////////////////

module ReplicateMod (
inout wire [3:0] bus,
inout wire [7:0] replicated
);
net_connect #(.WIDTH(8)) net_connect (replicated, ({2{bus}}));
endmodule : ReplicateMod


module tb;
logic [3:0] bus;
wire [7:0] replicated;
wire [3:0] wire__bus; assign wire__bus = bus;
ReplicateMod dut(.bus(wire__bus), .replicated(replicated));
initial begin
#1
bus = 4'h3;
#2
if(replicated !== 8'h33) $error($sformatf("Expected replicated=00110011, but found replicated=0x%x with inputs {bus: 0011}", replicated));
#8
bus = 4'hc;
#2
if(replicated !== 8'hcc) $error($sformatf("Expected replicated=11001100, but found replicated=0x%x with inputs {bus: 1100}", replicated));
#8
$finish;
end
endmodule
```

Are there plans to support this in Icarus Verilog?  I didn't see any other open issues tracking this, sorry if it is a duplicate.

